                                  INSTALLATION

Just type "make", followed by "make install". This will install all the
necessary files in your home directory. Other directories can be specified by
calling make with the prefix variable, for example, "make prefix=/usr", followed
by "make prefix=/usr install".

                                  REQUIREMENTS

You will need the GLib and DBus-GLib libraries.
On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* libglib2.0-0 (>= 2.16)
* libdbus-glib-1-2

                               BUILD REQUIREMENTS

You will need the GLib and DBus-GLib development libraries and headers.
Additionally, you will need the pkg-config and gettext tools.
On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* libglib2.0-dev (>= 2.16)
* libdbus-glib-1-dev
* pkg-config
* gettext

                             OPTIONAL DEPENDENCIES

On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* libnice0
* libnm-glib0

                          OPTIONAL BUILD DEPENDENCIES

On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* libnice-dev
* libnm-glib-dev

